FIGS. 6(a) to 6(f) are diagrammatic views respectively showing a state where a disk is not warped relative to the beam axis of a light beam incident on an objective lens (FIG.6(a)), a state where a light beam is focused in a spot on a single bit by an objective lens in the state shown in FIG. 6(a), a state where a disk is warped ((FIG.6(c)), a state where the light beam is focused in a spot by the objective lens on a bit and an adjacent in the state shown in FIG. 6(c) bit because the tilt of the objective lens relative to the disk is not corrected ((FIG.6(d)), a state where the disk is warped and the position of the objective lens is changed for tilt correction ((FIG. 6(e)), and a state where crosstalk is avoided owing to the correction of the tilt of the objective lens in the state shown in FIG. 6(e) (FIG.6(f));


